cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.IR 

This paper focuses on response generation in multi-party chatbots, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel model that incorporates interlocutor-aware contexts, which involves modeling the relationships between different interlocutors and their roles. This could fall under the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the construction of a corpus for the task, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
